Ramin,

Thanks for showing some interest here in improving testing.  I left some comments throughout.

I think my biggest hang-up on it is understanding the added value of mocking out dbus services.  To me, it seems like quite a bit of extra work over mocking at the "just before I call dbus" level, but not a significant value add.  This may give you issues with limited adoption.

Having said that, it looks like you're primarily focused on the dbus-client side of things.  We don't currently have generated client-bindings for sdbusplus like we do for the server side but I'm working on that.  Without the generated client-bindings there is some amount of manual formulation of dbus parameters that could maybe benefit from testing, but I'm hoping that that goes away over the next year.

Feel free to catch me on IRC sometime next week if you want to have some back and forth.

> So, how do we send this upstream to Yocto/OE?

Yocto contains a bunch of subrepositories, similar to how we use to do subtrees for various meta-layers, so you need to figure out which repository a particular file comes from.

In this case, it comes from 'OE-Core', so see https://git.openembedded.org/openembedded-core/about/

If you want to know where a file comes from you can clone Yocto's `poky` repo and run git log on the file and you'll see something like:

```
commit 433201369e3d8336335d052eea32fe64e811f6e6
Author: Mingli Yu <mingli.yu@windriver.com>
Date:   Mon Oct 11 16:28:48 2021 +0800

    packagedata.py: silence a DeprecationWarning
    
    Use regex strings (r’’) to silence below deprecation warning [1]:
     $ cat tmp/work/intel_x86_64-wrs-linux/linux-yocto/5.10.x+gitAUTOINC+917c420111_373c02c3ca-r0/temp/log.do_deploy
     [snip]
     /build/layers/oe-core/meta/lib/oe/packagedata.py:22: DeprecationWarning: invalid escape sequence \s
     r = re.compile("(^.+?):\s+(.*)")
     [snip]
    
    [1] https://docs.python.org/3/library/re.html
    
    (From OE-Core rev: b5b70cba70067466da5e94f69632a2a029203838)
    
    Signed-off-by: Mingli Yu <mingli.yu@windriver.com>
    Signed-off-by: Richard Purdie <richard.purdie@linuxfoundation.org>
```

So... not only is the file in OE-Core but it looks like someone already fixed it.  This means it should be picked up by Andrew's subtree commit that he is working on getting cleared.
